Pre-Game Insights: The match between Senegal and Malawi is part of the 3rd round of qualifiers for the CAN 2025.
Senegal aims to reclaim the first place from Burkina Faso, who defeated Burundi 4-1.
This will be the first match for Senegal without their long-time coach Aliou Cissé, who has been replaced by interim coach Pape Thiaw.
Senegal's captain Kalidou Koulibaly emphasized the importance of winning to honor their former coach and please the Senegalese people.
Senegal has a complete squad except for Abdallah Sima, who is injured and has returned to his club.
